kairo core/include
=================

overview
========

the `core/include` directory is a critical component of the kairo project, containing all the `.h` files that define the c++ core of the kairo runtime. these files provide the foundational c++ definitions required to support the kairo compiler and runtime system.

this directory acts as the bridge between the kairo language and its underlying c++ implementation, ensuring seamless integration and high performance.

purpose and functionality
=========================

- **c++ core definitions**:
  - this directory contains all the header files defining the core functionality of the kairo runtime in c++.
  - these definitions are essential for the compiler and runtime to function correctly.

- **compiler dependency**:
  - the kairo compiler relies on the definitions in this directory to translate kairo code into executable binaries.

- **seamless integration**:
  - the header files in this directory are tightly integrated with the kairo compiler and runtime, providing a robust and efficient foundation for all kairo programs.

warning
=======

- **critical directory**:
  - this directory and its files are essential for the kairo runtime and compiler.
  - do not remove or ignore this directory when configuring or building the kairo project.

